    <item>
      <title>Securinets Quals CTF: Cloud Infrastructure</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/securinets-quals-ctf-cloud-infrastructure/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mohamedmasmoudi745@gmail.com (Mohamed Masmoudi)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/securinets-quals-ctf-cloud-infrastructure/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As part of a team, I co-designed and deployed the full cloud infrastructure for the &amp;ldquo;Securinets Quals&amp;rdquo; international CTF. This project was a significant technical challenge focused on building a high-availability, scalable, and fault-tolerant system to handle heavy, unpredictable traffic from over 1,200 teams.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;infrastructure-overview&#34;&gt;Infrastructure Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The architecture was split into two main components: the core CTF platform and the challenge hosting environment, both designed for resilience.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-core-platform-ctfd&#34;&gt;1. Core Platform (CTFd)&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This was the main web application where players registered and submitted flags.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
